[B] India
Date: Fri 11 Jun 2021 10:05 IST
Source: The Times of India (TOI), Times News Network (TNN) [edited]
https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/covid-19india-reports-91702-new-cases-3403-deaths-in-last-24-hours/articleshow/83423000.cms


India on Friday [11 Jun 2021] reported 91 702 daily new COVID-19 cases, pushing the country's total tally to 29 274 823, according to the data updated by the Union health ministry. This is the 4th day in a row when the daily new cases are below one lakh [100 000].

With 3403 more deaths in the last 24 hours, the death toll has climbed to 363 079. On Thursday [10 Jun 2021], India registered a record daily rise of 6148 deaths from COVID-19. The death tally was the highest-ever because it included Bihar's previously uncounted 3951 deaths. If we discount Bihar's revised toll, a total of 2197 deaths were reported in the last 24 hours.

On Thursday [10 Jun 2021], India registered deaths of 6148 people attributed to COVID-19, the highest single-day count ever from the country. This count was because of adding the previously uncounted deaths of 3951 people from Bihar state. It is unsure whether any such backlog deaths remain to be counted from any other states to amend the official COVID-19 deaths so far.

Meanwhile, the active caseload has further declined to 1 121 671. The recovery rate has increased to 94.93%. A total of 134 580 patients were discharged yesterday [10 Jun 2021], taking the total recovery numbers to 27 790 073.

While the weekly positivity rate is currently at 5.14%, the daily positivity rate stands at 4.49%, less than 10% for 18 consecutive days, show data. According to ICMR [Indian Council of Medical Research], 37.42 crore [374 200 000] samples have been tested for COVID-19 so far. Of this, 2 044 131 samples were tested yesterday [10 Jun 2021].

