[D] Sri Lanka
Date: Thu 10 Jun 2021 01:05 IST
Source: The Daily Mirror [edited]
http://www.dailymirror.lk/breaking_news/Highest-single-day-COVID-19-deaths-reported/108-213786


A total of 67 more COVID-19 related fatalities were confirmed by the Director-General of Health Services recording the highest single-day tally.

According to the Government Information Department, 19 deaths have been reported between the period of 17-31 May 2021 while 48 deaths have been reported 1-8 Jun 2021.

It said 43 males and 24 females are among the deceased. Accordingly, the death toll in the country surged to 1910.

