[Data by country, area, or territory for 10 Jun 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20JUNE10_1623437175.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 40.1% of daily case numbers and 36.2% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 68.93 million cases. Brazil reported over 52 000 cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Argentina (31 137), Columbia (18 586), and the USA (16 551); 11 additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours (Canada, Chile, Peru, Venezuela, Paraguay, Mexico, Dominican Republic, Costa Rica, Uruguay, Bolivia, and Cuba), and 3 additional countries (Ecuador, Panama, and El Salvador) reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 13.4% of daily case numbers and 9.1% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 54.82 million cases. Many countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Israel, Belgium (3 cases), Switzerland (one case), Hungary, and Kazakhstan, among others; 9 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, and an additional 4 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 8.0% of daily case numbers and 3.7% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 10.38 million cases. Iran reported the highest number of cases (10 598) over the last 24 hours, followed by Iraq, UAE, Tunisia, Oman, Afghanistan, Kuwait, Bahrain, Pakistan and Saudi Arabia. Egypt and Jordan reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 3.9% of daily case numbers and 1.6 % of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 3.60 million cases. South Africa (8889) reported the highest number of cases over last 24 hours, followed by Zambia. Namibia, Kenya, and Uganda reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Cameroon, Botswana, Reunion, Gabon, and Niger, among others, did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 4.5% of daily case numbers and 2.4% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 3.20 million cases. Malaysia reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 6200 cases), followed by Philippines, Japan, Mongolia, Cambodia, South Korea, and China.

- The South East Asia region reported 29.8% of the daily newly reported cases and 46.6% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 33.10 million cases. India is dominant, reporting over 94 000 cases, followed by Indonesia (7725), Nepal (3449), Sri Lanka (2735), Bangladesh (2537), and Thailand (2310).

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 10 Jun 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

